                <div class="tab-content custom-tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="about">
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">
                            The India International Institute of Democracy and Election Management (IIIDEM) was established in June 2011 by the Election Commission of India (ECI) to serve as a premier global centre for electoral training, research, and capacity building. It functions under the direct supervision of the ECI and operates from its independent campus in Dwarka, New Delhi, with the objective of enhancing professional competencies in election management and strengthening democratic institutions.</p>

                            <p  style="text-align: justify;">The institute fosters collaboration and partnerships with international organisations like the International Institute for Democracy and Electoral Assistance (International IDEA) and has signed MoUs with over 28 countries. IIIDEM’s vision emphasizes promoting credible, inclusive, and transparent elections through continuous learning, research, innovation, and international cooperation.</p>

                            <p><h2 style="text-align: left;">HISTORY</h2></p>
                           <p  style="text-align: justify;"> Inspired by India’s belief that free, fair and credible elections form the bedrock of a vibrant democracy, a need was felt for an Institute, which can continually keep the tools of election management and democracy sharp, ready, and up-to date and provide electoral machinery with skills, competencies and expertise to professionally manage the complex electoral processes.</p>

                            <p  style="text-align: justify;">It was also felt that such an Institute must also share India’s experience as the largest, most diverse and inclusive democracy in the world with other democracies and countries. Election Commission of India has built a robust electoral system over the years and an Institute under the aegis of ECI, can promote democracy and election management at global level. It can contribute to global knowledge, systems and practices in the field of democracy and election management.
                            </p>
                            <p  style="text-align: justify;">Thus, as a response to and recognition of the long-felt need for Institutionalization of training, capacity building and research & knowledge management in the field of democracy and election management, nationally and internationally, Election Commission of India established India International Institute of Democracy and Election Management (IIIDEM) on 17th June 2011.</p>

                            <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIDEM has steadily been expanding its national and international activities since its inception. The journey of IIIDEM so far can be divided into two phases, one between 2011-2018 when it functioned from Nirvachan Sadan and 2018- 2025 when it operated from the new campus, which was still being built.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="whatwedo">
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIIDEM conducts a broad spectrum of programs designed to strengthen electoral governance domestically and globally. Its domestic training programmes cover essential aspects of election administration, voter registration, electoral technology, inclusive elections, political finance, and voter education, supporting officials involved in India’s complex electoral processes. On the global training front, IIIDEM delivers capacity-building curricula for international EMBs, sharing best practices and operational expertise with election officials worldwide.</p>

                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIIDEM provides electoral assistance, engages in bilateral partnerships, and conducts training of trainers to create multiplier effects across election administrations. The institute undertakes comprehensive capacity building, including field projects and workshops addressing contemporary challenges such as disinformation and technology in elections. IIIDEM’s initiatives also include peer exchanges, seminars, and thematic conferences, like the India International Conference on Democracy and Election Management (IICDEM), which bring together EMBs, experts, and policymakers to foster shared learning, collaboration, and innovation in democratic processes.</p>

                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">Developing training and academic curriculum for various courses is an important responsibility of IIIDEM’s research and academic team. A well-structured training curriculum is essential for achieving meaningful learning outcomes and involves analysis, design, development, implementation and evaluation.</p>

                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIIDEM also uses virtual reality and simulation tools for practical training in electoral scenarios. Apart from a Research Advisory Board and its own academic faculty, IIIDEM works with various other reputed Academic Institutions to offer various short term and long-term academic courses.</p>

                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIIDEM also develops short courses, designed for working professionals on emerging topics like AI in Elections, Cybersecurity, Media Ethics, etc. Further, IIIDEM also offers Executive-Level Programs, tailored for senior election officials focusing on Strategic Planning, Crisis Management, Election Management Diplomacy. An IIIDEM Certification/ Accreditation, recognized by Election Management Bodies (EMBs) globally is also established.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="campus">
                        <p><h2 style="text-align: left;">Institutional Block  </h2></p>
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">The Institutional Block at IIIDEM spans 12,500 sqm and is designed to support large-scale training and academic engagements. It houses 6 training halls, 3 conference halls, 2 group discussion rooms, 2 computer labs, a library, media room, lounge, and 2 customizable activity halls—accommodating up to 550 trainees simultaneously. The infrastructure fosters an immersive learning environment, equipped with modern facilities for effective capacity building.</p>

                        <p><h2 style="text-align: left;">Hostel Block </h2></p>
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">The Ground + 7 floors hostel block aims to make the stay of the IIIDEM participants a pleasant and comfortable one. The hostel has 9 Studio apartments, 26 Twin rooms, 59 single rooms and a 15 seater dormitory and can house around 200 people simultaneously. The hostel is equipped with facilities such as a Kitchen with Dining hall of 90 capacity and Recreation facility including Gymnasium and an indoor game room.</p>

                        <p><h2 style="text-align: left;">Auditorium</h2></p>
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">The IIIDEM Auditorium spans an impressive 2405 square meters and is equipped with state-of-the-art audio-visual technology to enhance the event experience. With a grand seating capacity of 400+, it serves as an ideal venue for conferences, trainings, lectures, and ceremonial functions.</p>

                        <p><h2 style="text-align: left;">Library</h2></p>
                        <p  style="text-align: justify;">IIIDEM library offers over 3,700 printed books and an expansive digital resource collection. It is a pivotal academic and research hub, housing full-text access to more than 10 million journal articles, books, and primary sources related to Democracy, Election Management, World Affairs, Politics, International Relations and Indian Political System. The IIIDEM Library also focuses on archiving ECI publications.</p>

